# Copy this file to ".env.local" in the same folder as package.json, then paste your real key.
# Never commit .env.local — it stays on your machine (and in Vercel env settings for deploy).
#
# How to get a key (you must do this in your Google account):
# 1) https://console.cloud.google.com/ → create/select a project
# 2) Billing → link a billing account (Maps Platform requires it; free tier still applies)
# 3) APIs & Services → Library → enable "Maps JavaScript API" and "Places API"
# 4) APIs & Services → Credentials → Create credentials → API key → copy the key
# 5) Edit the key → restrict by HTTP referrer (e.g. http://localhost:3000/* and your Vercel URL)
#
# Docs: https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/get-api-key
#
# Preferred (server-side for API route):
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key_here

# Optional fallback (only if needed):
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key_here

# Optional for AdvancedMarker support (without this, app falls back to standard markers):
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_MAP_ID=your_google_map_id_here
